An example of using Babel in a build process with webpack or other bundlers to convert ES6 code into ES5:
```javascript
// webpack.config.js
module.exports = {
  entry: './src/index.js',
  output: {
    filename: 'bundle.js',
    path: __dirname + '/dist'
  },
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.js$/, // Apply Babel to all JavaScript files
        exclude: /node_modules/, // Exclude node_modules from transformation
        use: {
          loader: 'babel-loader',
          options: {
            presets: ['@babel/preset-env'] // Use the preset for transforming ES6+ to ES5
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};
```
In this example, Babel is configured to transform ES6+ code to ES5 using the '@babel/preset-env' preset when bundling with webpack.

Example of creating a simple Backbone.js model:
```javascript
