Example of a simple collapse/expand feature using JavaScript and CSS:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <style>
    .content {
      display: none;
    }
    .expanded .content {
      display: block;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="header" onclick="toggleContent(this)">Click to Expand/Collapse</div>
  <div class="content">
    Additional content goes here.
  </div>

  <script>
    function toggleContent(element) {
      element.classList.toggle('expanded');
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```
In this example, clicking on the header will toggle the 'expanded' class, which controls the visibility of the content.

